Using texPreview to create Carousel in Rmarkdown

Jonathan Sidi

2018-11-30

Source: vignettes/slickr.Rmd
slickr.Rmd
library(texPreview)
library(slickR)

objpath <- file.path(getwd(),"slickr_files/figure-html")

if(!dir.exists(objpath))
  dir.create(objpath,recursive = TRUE)

tex_opts$set(
  fileDir = objpath,
  returnType = 'html',
  imgFormat = 'svg'
  )

Kable Input


texPreview::texPreview(
  obj = knitr::kable(mtcars,'latex'),
  stem = 'kable-1'
)
#> Warning: 'texPreview' is deprecated.
#> Use 'tex_preview' instead.
#> See help("Deprecated") and help("texPreview-deprecated").
#> Warning: ImageMagick was built without librsvg which causes poor qualty of SVG rendering.
#> For better results use image_read_svg() which uses the rsvg package.

TeX Input


tab='
\\begin{tabular}{llr}
\\hline
\\multicolumn{2}{c}{Item} \\\\
\\cline{1-2}
Animal    & Description & Price (\\$) \\\\
\\hline
Gnat      & per gram    & 13.65      \\\\
          & each        & 0.01       \\\\
Gnu       & stuffed     & 92.50      \\\\
Emu       & stuffed     & 33.33      \\\\
Armadillo & frozen      & 8.99       \\\\
\\hline
\\end{tabular}'

texPreview(
  obj = tab,
  stem = 'tex-1'
)
#> Warning: 'texPreview' is deprecated.
#> Use 'tex_preview' instead.
#> See help("Deprecated") and help("texPreview-deprecated").
#> Warning: ImageMagick was built without librsvg which causes poor qualty of SVG rendering.
#> For better results use image_read_svg() which uses the rsvg package.

Carousel slickR htmlwidget 

slickR::slickR(
  obj = list.files(
    objpath,
    full.names = TRUE,
    pattern = 'svg'),
  width = '100%'
)
